description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Locally Employed Doctor in Breast Surgery (Surgical Oncology post - ST1/2 equivalent). This post is intended for a candidate who wishes to gain surgical experience in the areas of breast and plastic and reconstructive surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is particularly appropriate for applicants who are approaching core surgical training and interested in developing their knowledge and skills across a range of surgical areas. Candidates who have completed foundation training are welcomed to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Marsden NHS Trust has a well-established surgical program across all surgical specialities, and this is an excellent opportunity to increase experience in a centre of excellence for breast surgery. This post will be based at the Chelsea site and is available from February 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Marios Tasoulis, Consultant Breast Surgeon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marios.Tasoulis@rmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
